If you don&#x27;t mind setting the function on instances at construct time, you can use ES2016 class properties:<p><pre><code>    class x {
      a = wrapFunction(function() {})
    }
</code></pre>
This kind of use case is pretty well covered by ES2016 decorators as well (they&#x27;re a bit more general as they act on property descriptors, not just values):<p><pre><code>    class x {
      @functionWrapper
      a() {}
    }</code></pre>
